HEADWORD: Arillode
<hw>Ar"il*lode</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Arillus</ets>
+ Gr. <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A false
aril; an aril originating from the micropyle instead of from the funicle
or chalaza of the ovule. The mace of the nutmeg is an
arillode.</def>⟦br⟧
